'''Joel Robert Waterman''' (born January 24, 1996) is a Canadian [[Association football|soccer]] player who plays as a [[centre-back]], [[right-back]] or [[defensive midfielder]] for [[Chicago Fire FC|Chicago Fire]] of [[Major League Soccer]] and the [[Canada men's national soccer team|Canada national team]].

==Early life==
Waterman began playing soccer at age five with Aldergrove Youth SC.<ref name="canada">{{Canada Soccer player|id=13480|accessdate=2026-05-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aldergrovesoccer.com/2019/07/04/former-aysc-player-joel-waterman-playing-against-vancouver-whitecaps-july-24/|title=Former AYSC Player Joel Waterman Playing Against Vancouver Whitecaps July 24|date=July 4, 2019|work=Aldergrove YSC}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aldergrovestar.com/sports/aldergrove-entourage-swarms-bc-place-for-local-soccer-player-gone-pro/|title=Aldergrove entourage swarms BC Place for local player gone pro|date=July 31, 2019|work=[[Aldergrove Star]]|first=Sarah|last=Grochowski|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref> At age 12, he joined [[Langley United]].<ref name="being">{{Cite web|url=https://gospartans.ca/news/2020/7/7/sparta-being-joel-waterman.aspx|work=[[Trinity Western Spartans]]|date=July 7, 2017|title=Being Joel|first=Mark|last=Janzen|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref> Afterwards, he played with [[Surrey United SC]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://aftn.ca/get-to-know-your-tss-rovers-joel-waterman/|title=Get To Know Your TSS Rovers: Joel Waterman|date=April 18, 2017|work=Away from the Numbers|first=Michael|last=McColl|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref>

When he was 13, he made the British Columbia provincial team.<ref name=being /> In 2013, he represented British Columbia at the [[2013 Canada Summer Games]]<ref name=being /> and also had a brief trial with the [[Vancouver Whitecaps Academy]], but did not make the squad.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rds.ca/soccer/cfm/joel-waterman-la-constance-d-un-grand-neglige-1.16323070|title=Joel Waterman ou la constance d'un grand négligé|trans-title=Joel Waterman or the constancy of a great underdog|language=fr|first=Nicolas|last=Landry|date=October 22, 2022|work=[[Réseau des sports|RDS]]|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref>

==University career==
In 2014, he began attending [[Trinity Western University]], where he played for the [[Trinity Western Spartans|men's soccer team]],<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |date=2014-09-05 |title=TWU soccer: Spartan men aim for return to post-season |url=https://langleyadvancetimes.com/2014/09/05/twu-soccer-spartan-men-aim-for-return-to-post-season/ |access-date=2026-05-03 |website=Langley Advance Times |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://gospartans.ca/sports/mens-soccer/roster/joel-waterman/406|title=Joel Waterman TWU profile|work=[[Trinity Western Spartans]]|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref> committing to them when he was in Grade 11.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aldergrovestar.com/sports/aldergrove-athlete-now-able-to-play-as-himself-in-favourite-childhood-video-game|title=Aldergrove pro athlete now plays as himself in favourite childhood video game|date=April 1, 2020|work=[[Aldergrove Star]]|first=Sarah|last=Grochowski|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref> Ahead of his fifth season, he was named the team captain,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://49-sport.com/2020/10/28/wtrmn2/|work=49-sport|title=Trinity to History: Joel Waterman is paving a path for U SPORTS grads|date=October 28, 2020|first=Casey|last=Dobson|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref> and helped them win a Canada West silver medal and finished fourth at the National Championship.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gospartans.ca/news/2020/12/23/mens-soccer-alum-waterman-named-to-canadas-national-team-camp-squad.aspx|title=Alum Waterman named to Canada's national team camp squad|date=December 23, 2020|work=[[Trinity Western Spartans]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.twu.ca/news-events/news/twu-spartans-alum-joel-waterman-named-canadas-national-team-camp-squad|title=TWU Spartans alum Joel Waterman named to Canada's national team camp squad|date=January 20, 2021|work=[[Trinity Western University]]}}</ref> He was also named a Canada West First Team All Star that season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gospartans.ca/story.aspx?filename=10_31_2018_887&file_date=10/31/2018|date=October 31, 2018|title=Waterman named Canada West First Team All-Star|work=[[Trinity Western Spartans]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aldergrovestar.com/sports/aldergroves-joel-waterman-gets-an-invitation-to-the-national-soccer-team-training-camp/|title=Aldergrove's Joel Waterman gets an invitation to the national soccer team training camp|date=December 28, 2020|work=[[Aldergrove Star]]|first=Dan|last=Ferguson|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Early career===
In 2016, Waterman played in the US-based [[USL League Two|Premier Development League]] side [[Kitsap Pumas]] and made eleven league appearances,<ref name="16pdl">{{cite web |title=Joel Waterman 2016 PDL Stats |url=https://www.uslleaguetwo.com/roster_players/12440583?subseason=278141 |publisher=[[USL League Two|Premier Development League]]|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref> while also appearing in two [[US Open Cup]] matches.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.lapresse.ca/sports/soccer/2020-01-14/l-impact-acquiert-le-defenseur-central-joel-waterman|title=L'Impact acquiert le défenseur central Joel Waterman|trans-title=The Impact acquires central defender Joel Waterman|language=fr|date=January 14, 2020|work=[[La Presse (Montréal)|La Presse]]}}</ref> In 2017, Waterman played with Vancouver-based [[TSS FC Rovers]] in the PDL, where he made eleven appearances.<ref name="17pdl">{{cite web |title=Joel Waterman 2017 PDL Stats|url=https://www.uslleaguetwo.com/roster_players/18033337?subseason=376352 |publisher=[[USL League Two|Premier Development League]]|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref> In 2018, Waterman played for [[Calgary Foothills FC|Calgary Foothills]] in the PDL, making fourteen league appearances and another three in the playoffs as Foothills won the PDL Championship.<ref name="18pdl">{{cite web |title=Joel Waterman 2018 PDL Stats|url=https://www.uslleaguetwo.com/roster_players/24767475 |publisher=[[USL League Two|Premier Development League]]|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=December 12, 2018|url=https://nsxinetwork.com/pdl-pedigree-with-a-cpl-destiny-newly-drafted-joel-waterman-looks-to-bring-leadership-to-cavalry-fc/|title=PDL pedigree with a CPL destiny: Newly drafted Joel Waterman looks to bring leadership to Cavalry FC|first=Jacob|last=Noseworthy|work=NSXI Network|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref>

===Cavalry FC===
At the [[2018 CPL–U Sports Draft]], Waterman was drafted in the second round by [[Cavalry FC]] on November 13, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gospartans.ca/sports/msoc/2018-19/releases/CPL_Draft|title=Waterman selected by Cavalry FC in 2nd round of CPL draft|date=November 13, 2018|work=[[Trinity Western Spartans]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190326110634/http://www.gospartans.ca/sports/msoc/2018-19/releases/CPL_Draft|archive-date=March 26, 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref> Initially, he had not planned on declaring for the draft, instead looking at potentially going to Europe or the United States, however, two days before the registration deadline, he decided to register.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://canpl.ca/article/beyond-the-pitch-joel-waterman-on-the-cpl-u-sports-draft-europe-and-whats-next-for-his-career|title=Beyond the Pitch: Joel Waterman on the CPL-U SPORTS Draft, Europe and what's next for his career|date=December 19, 2022|work=[[Canadian Premier League]]|first=Mitchell|last=Tierney|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref> He officially signed with Cavalry on February 6, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://canpl.ca/article/cavalry-adds-u-sports-draftee-joel-waterman|date=February 6, 2019|title=Cavalry FC adds CPL-U SPORTS Draft pick Joel Waterman}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aldergrovestar.com/local-sports/aldergroves-golden-boy-poised-to-go-pro/#|title=Aldergrove's golden boy poised to go pro|date=February 11, 2019|work=[[Aldergrove Star]]|first=Sarah|last=Grochowski|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref>

Waterman made his professional debut for Cavalry in their inaugural game against [[York9 FC]] on May 4.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://aftn.ca/cavalry-fcs-inaugural-starting-11-where-are-they-now/|title=Cavalry FC's inaugural starting 11 – where are they now?|date=May 4, 2022|work=Away from the Numbers|first=Scott|last=Strasser|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref> He scored his first goal for Cavalry on October 5 against [[HFX Wanderers FC]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://aftn.ca/goals-from-unlikely-sources-as-cavalry-fc-shuts-out-hfx-wanderers/|title=Goals from unlikely sources as Cavalry FC shuts out HFX Wanderers|date=October 5, 2019|first=Scott|last=Strasser|work=Away from the Numbers|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref> He helped Cavalry win the Spring and Fall championships<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://btsvancity.com/2020/01/13/sources-cavalry-fcs-joel-waterman-moving-to-montreal-impact-in-a-historic-move-for-cpl/|title=Sources: Cavalry FC's Joel Waterman moving to Montreal Impact in a historic move for CPL|date=January 13, 2020|work=BTS Vancouver|first=Alexandre|last=Gangué-Ruzic|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref> and helped them reach the CPL finals, where they finished second,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.journaldequebec.com/2021/11/19/une-deuxieme-chance-pour-joel-waterman|title=CF Montréal: une deuxième chance pour Joel Waterman|trans-title=CF Montreal: a second chance for Joel Waterman|date=November 19, 2021|first=Dave|last=Levesque|language=fr|work=[[Le Journal de Québec]]|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref> where he was unable to play in the second leg after being sent off in the first leg for a hand ball.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://aftn.ca/au-revoir-et-bonne-chance-joel-cavalry-center-back-waterman-heads-to-montreal-impact-in-history-setting-transfer/|title=Au Revoir et Bonne Chance, Joel – Cavalry center back Waterman heads to Montreal Impact, in history-setting transfer|date=January 14, 2020|work=Away from the Numbers|first=Scott|last=Strasser|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref> In December 2019, Cavalry announced Waterman would return to the club for the 2020 season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://northerntribune.ca/cavalry-fc-waterman-adekugbe-2020/|title=Cavalry FC Re-Signs Waterman And Adekugbe|date=December 19, 2019|work=Northern Tribune|first=John|last=Jacques|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref>

===CF Montréal===

On January 14, 2020, Waterman transferred to [[Major League Soccer]] club [[Montreal Impact (2012–2020)|Montreal Impact]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://canpl.ca/article/words-cant-describe-it-waterman-revels-in-historic-move-to-montreal|title='Words can't describe it': Waterman revels in historic move to Montreal Impact|first=Armen|last=Bedakian|date=January 14, 2020|work=[[Canadian Premier League]]|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cbc.ca/sports/soccer/joel-waterman-cpl-first-player-to-be-sold-canada-soccer-1.5429630|title=Joel Waterman makes history, 1st CPL player to be sold to another league in move to Impact|date=January 16, 2022|work=[[CBC Sports]]|first=Neil|last=Davidson|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref> With this transfer, Waterman made history as the first ever player from the [[Canadian Premier League]] to be sold to an MLS club.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://canpl.ca/article/joel-waterman-becomes-1st-cpler-sold-to-mls-side-in-montreal-impact-deal|first=Marty|last=Thompson|date=January 14, 2020|title=Joel Waterman becomes 1st CPLer sold to MLS in Montreal Impact deal|work=[[Canadian Premier League]]|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://canpl.ca/article/4-reasons-why-joel-waterman-is-the-1st-cpler-moving-to-mls|first=Marty|last=Thompson|date=January 14, 2020|title=4 reasons why Joel Waterman is the 1st CPLer moving to MLS|work=[[Canadian Premier League]]|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref> He made his debut for the Impact on February 19 against [[Deportivo Saprissa|Saprissa]] in a [[2020 CONCACAF Champions League|CONCACAF Champions League]] match.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://theprovince.com/sports/soccer/mls/ballistic-ascent-of-aldergroves-joel-waterman-continues-with-canmnt-invite|title=Ballistic ascent of Aldergrove's Joel Waterman continues with CANMNT invite|first=J.J.|last=Adams|date=January 19, 2021|work=[[The Province]]|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref> He made his MLS debut for the Impact in their season opener against the [[New England Revolution]] on February 29.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ledevoir.com/sports/574346/joel-waterman-veut-profiter-de-l-opportunite-qui-s-offre-a-lui-avec-l-impact|title=Joel Waterman veut profiter de l'occasion qui s'offre à lui avec l'Impact|trans-title=Joel Waterman wants to take advantage of the opportunity offered to him with the Impact|language=fr|date=March 6, 2020|first=Michel|last=Lamarche|work=[[Le Devoir]]}}</ref> Upon completion of the [[2021 Major League Soccer season|2021 MLS season]], CF Montréal announced that they would be exercising the option on Waterman's contract for 2022.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.cfmontreal.com/news/cf-montreal-exercises-options-for-12-players|title=CF Montréal exercises options for 12 players|website=CF Montreal|date=November 30, 2021}}</ref>

In 2022, he became a regular starter for the club.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://onesoccer.ca/a/hes-done-enough-canmnt-legend-believes-joel-waterman-is-ready-for-canada-nod|title='He's done enough': CanMNT legend believes Joel Waterman is ready for Canada nod|date=October 8, 2022|work=[[OneSoccer]]|first=Alexandre|last=Gangué-Ruzic|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref> During the [[2022 Major League Soccer season|2022 season]], he scored his first goal for Montreal against [[Orlando City SC|Orlando City]] on May 7, netting the opener in an eventual 4-1 victory.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/recap-cf-montreal-4-orlando-city-sc-1|title=Recap: CF Montréal 4, Orlando City SC 1|date=May 7, 2022|work=[[Major League Soccer]]|first=Tristan|last=D'Amours|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref> On August 4, he scored in the fourth minute of stoppage time to secure a 2-1 win over the [[Columbus Crew]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/sports/soccer/article-waterman-nets-pivotal-goal-as-montreal-defeats-crew-2-1/|title=Waterman nets pivotal goal as Montreal defeats Crew 2-1|date=August 3, 2022|work=[[The Globe & Mail]]}}</ref> In March 2023 Waterman signed a new contract with Montreal through 2024, with an option for 2025.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Loris |first=Benito |date=2022-08-03 |title=jalalive |url=https://vidya-ayurveda.org/ |access-date=2026-05-03 |language=en-CA}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.cfmontreal.com/news/new-contract-for-defender-joel-waterman|title=New contract for defender Joel Waterman|date=March 23, 2023}}</ref> In November 2024, Waterman would sign a contract extension through the 2027 season, with an option for 2028.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.cfmontreal.com/news/contract-extension-for-defender-joel-waterman|title=Contract extension for Defender Joel Waterman|website=CF Montreal|date=November 20, 2024}}</ref>

===Chicago Fire===
In August 2025, Waterman was traded to [[Chicago Fire FC]] in exchange for $500,000 in [[General Allocation Money]] and $100,000 in performance-based money.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sportsnet.ca/mls/article/cf-montreal-trades-defender-joel-waterman-to-chicago-fire-fc-for-gam/|title=CF Montreal trades defender Joel Waterman to Chicago Fire FC for GAM|date=August 20, 2025|work=[[Sportsnet]]}}</ref>

==International career==
He was called up to the [[Canada men's national soccer team|Canadian senior national team]] for the first time for a national team camp in January 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ctvnews.ca/calgary/former-cavalry-fc-player-gets-national-team-call-up-1.5244601?cache=rcraxwqwejtlei%3FclipId%3D89680|title=Former Cavalry FC player gets national team call-up|date=December 24, 2020|work=[[CTV News]]|first=Jillian|last=Code|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref> He earned several more call-ups to the squad during 2021 and 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tsn.ca/joel-waterman-luca-koleosho-canada-world-cup-qatar-2022-canmnt-cf-montreal-espanyol-1.1851231|title=Uncapped Waterman, Koleosho head to CanMNT|date=September 20, 2022|work=[[The Sports Network|TSN]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.lapresse.ca/sports/soccer/2022-09-16/cf-montreal/joel-waterman-obtient-son-rappel-du-canada.php|title=Joel Waterman obtient son rappel du Canada|trans-title=Joel Waterman gets his recall from Canada|language=fr|date=September 16, 2022|work=[[La Presse (Montréal)|La Presse]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://northerntribune.ca/canada-roster-joel-waterman/|title=Former Cavalry Defender Joel Waterman Cracks World Cup Test Roster|date=September 16, 2022|work=Northern Tribune|first=John|last=Jacques|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref> On November 11, 2022, he made his debut for Canada in a friendly against [[Bahrain national football team|Bahrain]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://canpl.ca/article/former-cplers-waterman-macnaughton-make-canmnt-debuts-in-draw-vs-bahrain|title=Former CPLers Waterman, MacNaughton make CanMNT debuts in draw vs. Bahrain|date=November 11, 2022|work=[[Canadian Premier League]]|first=Mitchell|last=Tierney|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref> On November 13, Waterman was named to Canada's squad for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://onesoccer.ca/a/how-a-cpl-draft-pick-cavalry-booked-a-canmnt-spot-at-the-world-cup-cf-montreal-canada|title='You have to keep believing': How a CPL draft pick booked a CanMNT spot at the World Cup|date=October 14, 2022|work=[[OneSoccer]]|first=Alexandre|last=Gangué-Ruzic|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref>

In June 2024, Waterman was named to Canada's squad for the [[2024 Copa América]], as an injury replacement for [[Junior Hoilett]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tsn.ca/soccer/joel-waterman-to-replace-injured-junior-hoilett-on-canada-s-copa-america-roster-1.2135368|date=June 16, 2024|work=[[The Sports Network|TSN]]|title=Waterman to replace injured Hoilett on Canada's Copa America roster}}</ref> In July 2025, he was called up to Canada's team for the [[2025 CONCACAF Gold Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.onesoccer.ca/a/canmnt-announce-2025-conacaf-gold-cup-squad-roster-canada-soccer|date=July 5, 2025|title=CanMNT name full-strength squad for 2025 Concacaf Gold Cup|first=Mitchell|last=Tierney}}</ref> In May 2026, Waterman was named to Canada's 26-man squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://northerntribune.ca/world-cup-2026-canada-squad/|first=John|last=Jacques|date=May 29, 2026|title=Here’s The Canada World Cup Roster|work=Northern Tribune}}</ref>

